column5: That's an 11'6 meat stick that I use for chucking hardware..  Nothing like big river lakers to put some arc into it!!  thanks brah.
Yep, darkest ever fish for me.  This lake is reputed to have really dark fish..  Water is crystal clear too.  She might have been a deep roamer..
Thanks bud.  Big G couldn't make it out that time.  He's been having great success though..  Maybe he'll indulge us a little!
Sweet pics HD.  Truely enjoyed. TFS.
Thanks for all the replies guys..  More to come!
Gotta love the niagara! nice feesh.
Beautiful fish and even better pictures! Thanks for  posting. I'm absolutely drooling!
Quite the catch, gotta love the trout trifecta (browns/lakers/bows). Does that first one have a clipped dorsal fin? Stray NY fish?
Yep dorsal was clipped by the looks of it..  Which is a shame.  Didn't seem to affect it much.  I suppose the fish would have to learn to compensate quickly.  She sure was well fed.
Love the variety of species HD. Great stuff.
Great fish and pics there Fidel. Some real beauties
Solid winter dood!  Great pics.  I like seeing the Niagara lakers caught that way.

Hey gang,  Been a great winter. I'll let the pics do the talking.         Quillback      Berkley Ripple Shad with a 1/4oz jighead... deadly.          This big durtie followed right in...  I dropped again and she crushed it right at my feet.    One for Mark too..    He couldn't be happier..      Got into these trouts while chasing poikes..      Some darker, smaller, prettier lakers..          eelpout!    A PB for my brother in law.    My first Toronto pike through the ice!    Wallacio with a prime fish.  Good to meet you brother.      Almost stepped over this guy.  He munched away just feet from me as I was drifting..    Be safe out there.  cheers HD
Nice report there Fidel !!! Good to see ya in here again.Nice to see ya gettin a little muskrat love there too big boy   Paul
Great pictures Fidel.  Looks like you had a great winter season  You're not kidding about those lakers being dark
I thought it was a beaver?
Yep.. Fresh Toronto beaver LOL
Good to bump into you Fidel...let's get out again soon bro!
Thursday... your lake..  I'm bringing the float tube. LOL
looks like a muskrat  size and all.
Merc can't tell them apart unless he sees their tail...  Nice overview Fidel !!!
worth the wait!  Awesome
Great Fish! Especially the lakers.
I prefer the browns. Good stuff mon ami. Some beauty fish there.
This is great...but it's the report you make when you get back from south that I'm really looking forward too.  I still can't believe you got those browns! Awesome.
Awesome Fidel, glad to see you've been fishing!
awesome pictures and fish
Great report, lot's of good pics and huge catches! Thanks for taking the time to post!  MTBF
Great pics! That's a lot of nice fish! Thanks for sharing.
I know the tails are really good with maple syrop I knew it was a beaver, just checking to see if you guys were paying attention
I like the lakers from the rivers! Makes my walleye and perch look like mud. hehe
HOLY.....HD...  Ummmmmmmm.....SPEECHLESS.  Thats just amazing...that pic with the rod bent double...great shot.  Drooooooooling.
Great report, pics and fish Fidel Steelhead, lakers and browns aren't they a blast to catch Congrats dude Jacques
Wow, you've been busy!  Some great pics and great fish.  That one ice laker is black!  I thought we got some dark lakers up here but I've never see one so dark before.
Lots of nice fishes there Fidel  First Toronto ice pike i have seen reported.  Was Grant there taking the picture?  Great stuff
great report
Me neither..  thanks bud!
